<title>UK: Summary of new CBI UK economic forecasts.</title>
<headline>Summary of new CBI UK economic forecasts.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-08-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Following is a summary of revised forecasts of British economic indicators by the Confederation of British Industry (CBI), published on Friday (annual percentage changes unless otherwise stated, figures in brackets are the CBI's last forecasts, published in May):</p>
<p>				   1995#	     1996	   1997</p>
<p> Total GDP			2.5	    2.0 (2.0)    3.1 (3.0)</p>
<p> Manufacturing output	 2.2	    0.6 (1.0)    3.9 (4.0)</p>
<p> Consumer expenditure	 2.0	    3.2 (2.8)    4.0 (3.5)</p>
<p> Fixed investment	    -0.1	    2.6 (3.4)    5.0 (4.1)</p>
<p>of which -  </p>
<p> General government	  -2.1	  -8.0(-6.8)   -4.0 (-7.1)</p>
<p> Manufacturing		  5.3	   0.6 (5.8)    7.5  (4.4)</p>
<p> Private Dwellings	    0.7	  -0.4 (1.3)    5.7  (4.0)</p>
<p> Other			   -1.0	   7.2 (6.4)    6.5  (6.9)</p>
<p> Government consumption     1.3	   0.5 (0.9)    0.2  (0.6)</p>
<p> Exports(goods/services)    7.2	   6.1 (3.2)    4.8  (4.2)</p>
<p> Imports(goods/services)    3.9	   7.5 (3.7)    4.8  (4.6)</p>
<p> Current account (bln stg) -2.9	  -6.3(-6.0)   -9.6 (-6.8)</p>
<p> Stockbuilding (blns stg)   3.3	   2.9 (1.5)    2.6  (2.5)</p>
<p> Inflation (RPI) (Q4)	 3.2	   2.2 (2.4)    2.8  (2.5)</p>
<p> RPIX (Q4)			2.9	   2.6 (2.7)    2.5  (2.5)</p>
<p> Manuf output prices	  4.4	   2.1 (2.9)    2.6  (2.7)</p>
<p> Unemployment (millions)    2.2	   2.1 (2.1)    2.0  (2.0)</p>
<p> Company profits*	     2.2	   1.9 (5.2)    5.0  (5.5)</p>
<p> PSBR (blns stg)**	    32.1	  27.5 (26.1)  25.4 (23.5)</p>
<p># outturns using data from Office for National Statistics * Company profits are gross pre-tax trading profits of industrial and commercial companies, net of stock appreciation and excluding North Sea oil, and adjusted for inflation as measured by the GDP deflator. RPIX is retail prices excluding mortgage interest payments. ** PSBR data are for fiscal years.</p>
<p>-- Rosemary Bennett 44 171 542 7715</p>
